trans-unit.source: Indicates whether a control designer requires a preview instance of the control at design time.
trans-unit.target: Indica si un diseñador de controles requiere una instancia de vista preliminar del control en tiempo de diseño.

trans-unit.source: This class cannot be inherited.
trans-unit.target: Esta clase no puede heredarse.

trans-unit.source: Apply the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> attribute to a control designer class to indicate the type of preview control that is supported by the control designer.
trans-unit.target: Aplicar el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> atributo a una clase de diseñador de control para indicar el tipo de control de vista previa que sea compatible con el Diseñador de controles.

trans-unit.source: Use this attribute to change a preview control for design-time rendering without affecting the actual persisted instance of the associated control.
trans-unit.target: Utilice este atributo para cambiar un control de vista previa para la representación en tiempo de diseño sin afectar a la instancia almacenada real del control asociado.

trans-unit.source: Typically, you specify the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> when declaring a custom designer class that is derived from the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner> class.
trans-unit.target: Por lo general, especifique la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> al declarar una clase de diseñador personalizada que se deriva de la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner> clase.

trans-unit.source: The value of the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> property for the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> attribute determines the behavior for the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.UsePreviewControl%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.ViewControl%2A> members in the base <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner> class.
trans-unit.target: El valor de la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> propiedad para la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> atributo determina el comportamiento de la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.UsePreviewControl%2A> y <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.ViewControl%2A> los miembros de la base de <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner> clase.

trans-unit.source: Set the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> property to `true` to indicate that the designer uses a temporary copy of the associated control to generate the design-time HTML.
trans-unit.target: Establecer el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> propiedad `true` para indicar que el diseñador utiliza una copia temporal del control asociado para generar el código HTML en tiempo de diseño.

trans-unit.source: Changes to the temporary control are not persisted.
trans-unit.target: Cambios en el control temporal no se conservan.

trans-unit.source: Set the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> property to `false` to indicate that the designer returns the control instance, specifically the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.ComponentDesigner.Component%2A> property, from the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.ViewControl%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Establecer el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> propiedad `false` para indicar que el diseñador devuelve la instancia del control, específicamente el <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.ComponentDesigner.Component%2A> propiedad, desde el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.ViewControl%2A> método.

trans-unit.source: Changes to the control object are persisted.
trans-unit.target: Se conservan los cambios en el objeto de control.

trans-unit.source: For example, the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.CalendarDesigner> class is marked with the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> set to `true`.
trans-unit.target: Por ejemplo, el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.WebControls.CalendarDesigner> clase se marca con la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> establecido en `true`.

trans-unit.source: The designer uses the preview control with the automatic style formatting task, which allows the user to preview various autoformat stylesthat can be applied to the calendar.
trans-unit.target: El diseñador utiliza el control de vista previa con el estilo automática se pueden aplicar tareas de formato, que permite al usuario obtener una vista previa de diversos stylesthat Autoformato al calendario.

trans-unit.source: As the user selects different autoformat styles in the user interface, the selected style scheme is applied to the preview control.
trans-unit.target: Cuando el usuario selecciona diferentes estilos de Autoformato en la interfaz de usuario, el esquema de estilo seleccionado se aplica al control de vista previa.

trans-unit.source: Applying a new style to the preview control does not change the scheme that is applied to the instance of the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Calendar> control in the designer.
trans-unit.target: Aplicar un estilo nuevo para el control de vista previa no cambia el esquema que se aplica a la instancia de la <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Calendar> control en el diseñador.

trans-unit.source: If the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> is not specified in the control designer declaration, the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner> behavior is equivalent to specifying the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> as `false`.
trans-unit.target: Si el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> no se especifica en la declaración del Diseñador de control, el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner> comportamiento es equivalente a especificar la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> como `false`.

trans-unit.source: Designer classes derived from the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner> class can override the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.UsePreviewControl%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.ViewControl%2A> members, and ignore the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> attribute.
trans-unit.target: Las clases de diseñador que se derivan de la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner> clase puede invalidar la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.UsePreviewControl%2A> y <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.ViewControl%2A> miembros y pasar por alto el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> atributo.

trans-unit.source: To determine the expected behavior for <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.ViewControl%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.UsePreviewControl%2A>, see the reference documentation for the derived control designer class.
trans-unit.target: Para determinar el comportamiento esperado para <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.ViewControl%2A> y <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.UsePreviewControl%2A>, consulte la documentación de referencia de la clase de diseñador de control derivado.

trans-unit.source: For general information about using attributes, see [Attributes Overview](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/a4daf212-2410-423d-a800-7a08864e9bff) and [Attributes](~/docs/standard/attributes/index.md).
trans-unit.target: Para obtener información general sobre el uso de atributos, vea [Attributes Overview](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/a4daf212-2410-423d-a800-7a08864e9bff) y [atributos](~/docs/standard/attributes/index.md).

trans-unit.source: For more information about design-time attributes, see [Attributes and Design-Time Support](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7aed9eb4-124b-4a15-a0a3-458f37ac9ef7).
trans-unit.target: Para obtener más información acerca de los atributos de tiempo de diseño, vea [atributos y compatibilidad en tiempo de diseño](http://msdn.microsoft.com/library/7aed9eb4-124b-4a15-a0a3-458f37ac9ef7).

trans-unit.source: The following code example demonstrates how to mark a control designer with the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> attribute.
trans-unit.target: En el ejemplo de código siguiente se muestra cómo marcar un diseñador de controles con el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> atributo.

trans-unit.source: The code example derives an ASP.NET server control from the <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Label> class and associates the ASP.NET server control with a custom control designer implementation.
trans-unit.target: El ejemplo de código deriva un control de servidor ASP.NET desde el <xref:System.Web.UI.WebControls.Label> clase y asocia el control de servidor ASP.NET con una implementación del Diseñador de control personalizado.

trans-unit.source: The control designer class declaration is marked with the `SupportsPreviewControl` attribute set to `true`.
trans-unit.target: La declaración de clase de diseñador de control se marca con la `SupportsPreviewControl` atributo establecido en `true`.

trans-unit.source: The control designer overrides the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.GetDesignTimeHtml%2A> method and encloses the design-time HTML for the control in italic tags.
trans-unit.target: El Diseñador de control reemplaza el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.GetDesignTimeHtml%2A> método y agrega el código HTML en tiempo de diseño para el control en cursiva etiquetas.

trans-unit.source: The initial value to assign for <see cref="P:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl" />.
trans-unit.target: El valor inicial que se asigna a <see cref="P:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl" />.

trans-unit.source: Initializes a new instance of the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" /> class and sets the initial value of the <see cref="P:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl" /> property.
trans-unit.target: Inicializa una instancia nueva de la clase <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" /> y establece el valor inicial de la propiedad <see cref="P:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl" />.

trans-unit.source: Typically, you do not need to create an instance of the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> class directly.
trans-unit.target: Por lo general, no es necesario crear una instancia de la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> clase directamente.

trans-unit.source: Apply the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> to the class declaration of the custom control designer in the source code.
trans-unit.target: Aplicar el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> a la declaración de clase del Diseñador de control personalizado en el código fuente.

trans-unit.source: Gets an instance of the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" /> class that is set to the default preview value.
trans-unit.target: Obtiene una instancia de la clase <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" /> establecida en el valor de vista preliminar predeterminado.

trans-unit.source: This field is read-only.
trans-unit.target: Este campo es de solo lectura.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> property of the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.Default> field is set to `false`.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> propiedad de la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.Default> campo está establecido en `false`.

trans-unit.source: Use the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.IsDefaultAttribute%2A> method to determine whether the value for the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> property is set to the default preview value.
trans-unit.target: Use la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.IsDefaultAttribute%2A> método para determinar si el valor de la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> propiedad está establecida en el valor de vista previa de forma predeterminada.

trans-unit.source: The object to compare with the current instance of <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" />.
trans-unit.target: Objeto que se va a comparar con la instancia actual de <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" />.

trans-unit.source: Determines whether the specified object represents the same preview attribute setting as the current instance of the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" /> class.
trans-unit.target: Determina si el objeto especificado representa la misma configuración de atributo de vista preliminar que la instancia actual de la clase <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" />.

trans-unit.source: <see langword="true" /> if <paramref name="obj" /> is a <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" /> attribute and its value is the same as this instance of <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" />; otherwise, <see langword="false" />.
trans-unit.target: Es <see langword="true" /> si <paramref name="obj" /> es un atributo <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" /> y tiene el mismo valor que la instancia de <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" />; en caso contrario, es <see langword="false" />.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.Equals%2A> method overrides the <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.Equals%2A> reemplazos de método la <xref:System.Object.Equals%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> método.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.Equals%2A> method compares two instances based on the value of their <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> properties.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.Equals%2A> método compara dos instancias basándose en el valor de sus <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> propiedades.

trans-unit.source: Returns the hash code for this instance of the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" /> class.
trans-unit.target: Devuelve el código hash de esta instancia de la clase <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" />.

trans-unit.source: A 32-bit signed integer hash code for the current instance of <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" />.
trans-unit.target: Un código hash entero con signo de 32 bits para la instancia actual de <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" />.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.GetHashCode%2A> method overrides the <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> method.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.GetHashCode%2A> reemplazos de método la <xref:System.Object.GetHashCode%2A?displayProperty=nameWithType> método.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.GetHashCode%2A> method generates the same hash code for two objects that are equal according to the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.Equals%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.GetHashCode%2A> método genera el mismo código hash para dos objetos que son iguales de acuerdo con la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.Equals%2A> método.

trans-unit.source: The hash code is suitable for use in hashing algorithms and data structures, such as hash tables.
trans-unit.target: El código hash es adecuado para su uso en algoritmos hash algoritmos y estructuras de datos, como las tablas hash.

trans-unit.source: Indicates whether the current instance of the <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" /> class is set to the default preview attribute value.
trans-unit.target: Indica si la instancia actual de la clase <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" /> está establecida en el valor del atributo de la vista preliminar predeterminado.

trans-unit.source: <see langword="true" /> if the current instance of <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" /> is equal to the default preview attribute value; otherwise, <see langword="false" />.
trans-unit.target: Es <see langword="true" /> si la instancia actual de <see cref="T:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute" /> es igual al valor del atributo de la vista preliminar predeterminado; de lo contrario, es <see langword="false" />.

trans-unit.source: The <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.IsDefaultAttribute%2A> method compares the value for the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> property of the current <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> object with the value for the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> property of the static <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.Default> field.
trans-unit.target: El <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.IsDefaultAttribute%2A> método compara el valor de la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> propiedad del elemento actual <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> objeto con el valor de la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> propiedad de los métodos estático <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.Default> campo.

trans-unit.source: Gets a value indicating whether the control designer requires a temporary preview control at design time.
trans-unit.target: Obtiene un valor que indica si el diseñador de controles requiere un control de vista preliminar temporal en tiempo de diseño.

trans-unit.source: <see langword="true" /> if the designer uses a temporary copy of the associated control for design-time preview; <see langword="false" /> if the designer uses an instance of the <see cref="P:System.ComponentModel.Design.ComponentDesigner.Component" /> control that is contained in the designer.
trans-unit.target: Es <see langword="true" /> si el diseñador utiliza una copia temporal del control asociado para la vista preliminar en tiempo de diseño; es <see langword="false" /> si el diseñador utiliza una instancia del control <see cref="P:System.ComponentModel.Design.ComponentDesigner.Component" /> contenido en el diseñador.

trans-unit.source: Typically, you specify a value for the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> property by applying the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> attribute to a custom designer class declaration.
trans-unit.target: Normalmente, se especifica un valor para el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> propiedad aplicando el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> atributo a una declaración de clase de diseñador personalizada.

trans-unit.source: The value of the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> property for the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> attribute determines the behavior for the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.UsePreviewControl%2A> and <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.ViewControl%2A> members in the base <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner> class.
trans-unit.target: El valor de la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> propiedad para la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute> atributo determina el comportamiento de la <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.UsePreviewControl%2A> y <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.ViewControl%2A> los miembros de la base de <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner> clase.

trans-unit.source: Set the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> property to `true` to indicate that the designer uses a temporary copy of the associated control to generate the design-time HTML.
trans-unit.target: Establecer el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> propiedad `true` para indicar que el diseñador utiliza una copia temporal del control asociado para generar el código HTML en tiempo de diseño.

trans-unit.source: Changes to the temporary control are not persisted.
trans-unit.target: Cambios en el control temporal no se conservan.

trans-unit.source: Set the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> property to `false` to indicate that the designer returns the control instance, specifically the <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.ComponentDesigner.Component%2A> property, from the <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.ViewControl%2A> method.
trans-unit.target: Establecer el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.SupportsPreviewControlAttribute.SupportsPreviewControl%2A> propiedad `false` para indicar que el diseñador devuelve la instancia del control, específicamente el <xref:System.ComponentModel.Design.ComponentDesigner.Component%2A> propiedad, desde el <xref:System.Web.UI.Design.ControlDesigner.ViewControl%2A> método.

trans-unit.source: Changes to the control object are persisted.
trans-unit.target: Se conservan los cambios en el objeto de control.
